  .slide
    p.em-above: :t
      Suppose we reject the view that humans’ capacities to track agents and their actions
      (i) all involve just one model, and (ii) come with construals that are widely-shared among humans.
    p.em-above: :t
      Can we still ask the ‘fundamental question’ of action theory?
