    .notes: :t
      My sense is that the action term as used by philosophers to pose a ‘fundamental question’
      rests on the view that humans have a capacity to track agents and their actions
      which (i) involves a single model, and (ii) comes with construals that are widely-shared among humans.
    .notes: :t
